tweet: This only shows confirmed dates and $AMD hasn't scheduled their earnings yet. We suspect they will report on 7/27.  $GOOGL is confirmed for 7/27, but our users are currently more interested in the others listed for that date and didn't make the graphic.

Perhaps you shouldn't use $AMZN's guidance as a macro gauge since it seldom gives "positive" guidance and has given guidance below estimates four of the past six quarters.  The last time the company gave guidance above estimates was April 2011.
$AAPL will probably react more to 4th Q guidance than results.  Estimates are for negative growth, but data checks appear to be turning higher
Retailers will report January sales on Thursday, but $LB reports earnings after the close on 2/27
Since $AAPL's 1Q results are known, the focus will be on guidance, which we have at $2.32 per share on revenue of $57.0 billion - below the consensus of $2.64 on revenue of $59.0 billion

Bulkowski's target for a Bump-and-Run Reversal suggests $110 for $AAPL.  The trough forward PE multiple would take the stock to $114 (using current estimates that are going lower).  The positive is that most analysts already downgraded the stock.
